  <title>Tapenade (Olive Spread)</title>
  </head>
  
  <body>
  <p>This is a really simple dish to prepare and it's always a big hit at parties.  May father recommends:</p>
  <p>"Make this the night before so that the flavors have time to blend.  Just bring it up to room temperature before you serve it.  In the winter, try serving it warm."</p>
  <h1>Ingredients</h1>
  <p>Combine tomatoes and garlic in a food processor.  lend until as smooth as possible</p>
  <p>Add capers and olive.  Pulse the motor a few times util they are incorporated, but still retain some texture.</p>
  <p>Serve on thin toast rounds with goat cheese and fresh basil garnish (optional).</p>
